<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-010-290 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 521 638</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Nov 18 1991 v8 n46 p11(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC forms council to monitor outages; users are tentativelypleased with commission's effort but question impact of anadvisory group. (US Federal Communications Commission Chmn AlfredSikes at the National Association of Regulatory Utility Commissionannual conference)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wallace, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>US Federal Communications Commission (FCC) Chmn Alfred Sikes tellsthe annual conference of the National Association of RegulatoryUtility Commissions that the FCC plans to create theTelecommunications Reliability Council (TRC) to work with localand interexchange carriers to limit service interruptions.andP;  TheTRC will be made up of users, carriers, equipment vendors andstate regulators; its creation is motivated in large part by aseries of recent service outages on the East Coast of the US.andP;  FCCDeputy Chief of Operations Gerry Vaughan says the TRC will likelystudy the network infrastructures of carriers, identify areasrequiring improvement and suggest corrective action; Vaughan saysthe group will act as an advisory council to the FCC.andP;  Users arepleased with the announcement, but they say they need to know moreabout the council's composition, its power and mission statement.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Government AgencyInvestigationsCommunications IndustryTelecommunicationsCommunications Service SuppliersConferences and MeetingsGovernment RegulationUtilitiesUser NeedsPower FailureUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionNational Association of Regulatory Utility Commissioners.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>